task_description: Search for Economy class flights from VIE to MCO for 2 adult passengers for the date range July 28th-31st, 2026. What is the total price for the cheapest departure and return flight?

subtasks.name: Open Google Flights
subtasks.description: Open a browser and navigate to Google Flights search page

subtasks.name: Switch to Target Tab
subtasks.description: Switch focus to the tab where the flight search UI is open

tab_id.description: Identifier of the browser tab to switch to (e.g., 'tab-002')

subtasks.name: Set Number of Adult Passengers
subtasks.description: Open passenger selector, add adults, and confirm selection

num_adults_to_add.description: How many times to click 'Add adult' to reach desired adult count (e.g., add 1 to go from 1 to 2 adults)

subtasks.name: Enter Departure Airport
subtasks.description: Open the 'Where from' field, type a departure query, and select the desired airport from suggestions

departure_query.description: Text typed into the departure field to find the origin (e.g., 'Vienna VIE')

departure_airport_choice.description: The specific suggestion/airport to click (e.g., 'Vienna International Airport (VIE)')

subtasks.name: Enter Destination Airport
subtasks.description: Open the 'Where to' field, type a destination query (optionally refine), and select the desired airport from suggestions

destination_query_1.description: Initial text typed into the destination field (e.g., 'Orlando MCO')

destination_query_2.description: Optional refinement text typed into the destination field (e.g., 'MCO')

destination_airport_choice.description: The specific suggestion/airport to click (e.g., 'Orlando International Airport (MCO)')

subtasks.name: Set Round-Trip Dates
subtasks.description: Open date picker, enter departure and return dates, submit, and confirm done

subtasks.name: Run Flight Search
subtasks.description: Trigger the flight search after all criteria are set

results.reasoning: This action group contains multiple reusable UI interaction patterns for Google Flights: opening the site, selecting passengers, entering origin/destination, setting round-trip dates, and running the search. These can be parameterized with airport queries/choices and dates for reuse across many flight-search workflows.
